\cf6 \uc0\u9210 \cf3  Good instinct to revisit this. The Vail test actually exposes two separate    \
  issues that are getting conflated:                                            \
                                                                                \
  
\f1\b Issue 1 \'97 Coordinate bias.
\f0\b0  Open-Meteo is returning 0" at Vail's base lodge    \
  coordinates (8,120 ft) in late March. That's probably accurate at base        \
  elevation, but Vail is still operating \'97 there's snow at 10,000+ ft. The 0"   \
  reading is partly an artifact of querying at the lowest point of the mountain.\
\
  
\f1\b Issue 2 \'97 What snow depth should actually control.
\f0\b0  Right now depth does two   \
  jobs: it determines 
\f2\i whether
\f0\i0  a resort is open, and 
\f2\i how good
\f0\i0  conditions are.\
  Those are different questions and probably shouldn't be answered by the same  \
  variable.                                                 \
\
  
\f1\b My recommendation \'97 separate the two concerns:
\f0\b0                                 \
   \
  - 
\f1\b "Is the resort open?"
\f0\b0  \uc0\u8594  use \cf10 season_open\cf3  / \cf10 season_close\cf3  from the CSV as a    \
  binary feasibility check. If today's date is within season, the resort is\
  operating. That's a hard exclude.                                             \
  - 
\f1\b "How good are conditions?"
\f0\b0  \uc0\u8594  use snow depth purely to score quality, no hard\
   exclude. Extend the scale downward:                                          \
   \
  0"\'9624"   \uc0\u8594   0.0\'960.1   (warning: very thin base, groomed runs only likely)     \
  24"\'9630"  \uc0\u8594   0.1\'960.2   (etc., shift everything up slightly)                    \
                                                                                \
  This way a late-season resort with 10" of base scores low (as it should) but  \
  isn't zeroed out \'97 some groomed terrain is genuinely still accessible.        \
                                                                                \
  The rescue clause stays as-is since fresh snow on a thin base is still        \
  meaningful.\
                                                                                \
  Does that framing make sense to you, or do you want to keep the hard exclude  \
  but just adjust the threshold?\
